      <resourceConstraints>
        <MD_Constraints>
          <useLimitation>
            <gco:CharacterString>We do not guarantee the location accuracy of this dataset. When utilizing the products from this project, the accuracy and other limitations of the two PLSS shape files that were used to spatially reference the plat images need to be taken into account. The plat maps were hand drawn in the 1800s using field notes from surveyors using compass and chain. The plats are almost 200 years old and were scanned to produce an electronic record. This process could have also introduced error. These images were then brought into GIS software where they were warped and transformed to fit onto a Cartesian coordinate system. The measurements found in the original surveyors' field notes take precedence over plat drawings. Users need to keep in mind that any location error that occurred at any stage was compounded throughout this process. This product should not be used to legally define property or any other critical decision making process.Federal and State Law prohibits the looting of archeological sites. This GIS product should not be used for such activity. If anyone is to find anything of archeological significance, they should contact their local archeologist.</gco:CharacterString>
          </useLimitation>
        </MD_Constraints>
      </resourceConstraints>
